as indeed implemented the local ASR path. I think it's important to note that the documentation might be outdated; that could lead to some confusion. I should also consider referencing proof from source files that indicate changes. Additionally, checking the model manager could provide insight into the model readiness conditions, which seems relevant. Overall, there are a few important details to clarify moving forward!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Ged0YRZ3aaDLwFWvmG93y7l6|fc_04b76fdf640436710169b757090d9c81a092fed0b1cce50479","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/apps/kids-box-tv-app/app/src/main/java/com/openclaw/kidsboxtv/data/SherpaOnnxModelManager.kt","offset":1,"limit":220},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/apps/kids-box-tv-app/app/src/main/java/com/openclaw/kidsboxtv/data/SherpaOnnxModelManager.kt\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":220}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3299,"output":105,"cacheRead":56448,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59852,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773623042597}}
{"type":"message","id":"4da51b9d","parentId":"1619752b","timestamp":"2026-03-16T01:04:09.869Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Ged0YRZ3aaDLwFWvmG93y7l6|fc_04b76fdf640436710169b757090d9c81a092fed0b1cce50479","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"package com.openclaw.englishworkbook.data\n\nimport android.content.Context\nimport java.io.File\n\nclass SherpaOnnxModelManager(context: Context) {\n    private val appContext = context.applicationContext\n\n    fun defaultModelId(): String = \"english-zipformer-small\"\n\n    fun canonicalModelId(modelId: String): String {\n        return when (modelId.trim()) {\n            \"\", \"english-small\" -> defaultModelId()\n            else -> modelId.trim()\n        }\n    }\n\n    fun modelsRootDir(): File {\n        return File(appContext.filesDir, \"sherpa-onnx\")\n    }\n\n    fun ensureModelsRootDir(): File {\n        return modelsRootDir().apply { mkdirs() }\n    }\n\n    fun modelDir(modelId: String): File {\n        return File(ensureModelsRootDir(), canonicalModelId(modelId))\n    }\n\n    fun ensureModelDir(modelId: String): File {\n        return modelDir(modelId).apply { mkdirs() }\n    }\n\n    fun requiredFiles(modelId: String): List<String> {\n        return when (canonicalModelId(modelId)) {\n            defaultModelId() -> listOf(\n                \"tokens.txt\",\n                \"encoder.onnx\",\n                \"decoder.onnx\",\n                \"joiner.onnx\",\n            )\n            else -> listOf(\n                \"tokens.txt\",\n                \"encoder.onnx\",\n                \"decoder.onnx\",\n                \"joiner.onnx\",\n            )\n        }\n    }\n\n    fun inspect(modelId: String): SherpaOnnxModelStatus {\n        val canonicalId = canonicalModelId(modelId)\n        val dir = ensureModelDir(canonicalId)\n        val required = requiredFiles(canonicalId)\n        val missing = required.filterNot { File(dir, it).isFile }\n        return SherpaOnnxModelStatus(\n            modelId = canonicalId,\n            modelDirPath = dir.absolutePath,\n            requiredFiles = required,\n            missingFiles = missing,\n        )\n    }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773623049858}}
