og my self-improvement using a tool called self_improvement_log. It seems like a simpler option for tracking progress. I should also log the correction to address the concern properly. I can do this in commentary format without adding too much narration, keeping it straightforward while still being effective in my response.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_GZtSkvmXlvAW8PQJJgi7fth5|fc_04b76fdf640436710169b75815b04c81a0b8afff906319219a","name":"self_improvement_log","arguments":{"type":"learning","area":"docs","category":"correction","priority":"high","summary":"Do not claim 'I’ll continue pushing app optimization myself' without verifiable follow-through in the stated time window","details":"User pointed out that I said I would keep advancing the app optimization, but inspection showed no app commits or source/doc changes between 2026-03-16 00:00 and 07:30. This created a trust gap because I implied ongoing execution without evidence.","suggestedAction":"When reporting progress, explicitly separate completed work from intended next steps. If no new work happened, say so directly. Do not imply autonomous continuation unless there is concrete evidence in git/files/logs from the claimed window."},"partialJson":"{\"type\":\"learning\",\"area\":\"docs\",\"category\":\"correction\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"summary\":\"Do not claim 'I’ll continue pushing app optimization myself' without verifiable follow-through in the stated time window\",\"details\":\"User pointed out that I said I would keep advancing the app optimization, but inspection showed no app commits or source/doc changes between 2026-03-16 00:00 and 07:30. This created a trust gap because I implied ongoing execution without evidence.\",\"suggestedAction\":\"When reporting progress, explicitly separate completed work from intended next steps. If no new work happened, say so directly. Do not imply autonomous continuation unless there is concrete evidence in git/files/logs from the claimed window.\"}"}],"api":"