earch strategy**\\n\\nI see that I should provide evidence of my ongoing work with tool calls and potentially combine it with a web search. I need to select the appropriate skill, and it seems like I can choose multiple ones. Given the user's request to find资料, the markdown-mirror-search or deep-research-pro seems most suitable. The markdown-mirror-search is perfect for searching the web, reading webpages, and gathering info. I can read SKILL.md for confirmation, and then proceed!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_oDc04E4ZobnHpTRE6p0DpyJY|fc_04b76fdf640436710169b76091cdf881a089976495b0409acd","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/skills/markdown-mirror-search/SKILL.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/skills/markdown-mirror-search/SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1527,"output":386,"cacheRead":116096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118009,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773625473382}}
{"type":"message","id":"a43ef078","parentId":"ddf5688a","timestamp":"2026-03-16T01:44:50.720Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_oDc04E4ZobnHpTRE6p0DpyJY|fc_04b76fdf640436710169b76091cdf881a089976495b0409acd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: markdown-mirror-search\ndescription: \"Use when the user asks to search the web, read webpages, convert a URL into readable markdown/text, scrape article content, or gather information from websites without relying on raw page HTML. For search requests, use web search first to find candidate URLs, then extract readable content with this skill. Prefer mirror services in this order: (1) markdown.new for the original URL, especially when Cloudflare-backed pages work there, (2) defuddle.md for a second markdown extraction pass, (3) r.jina.ai for plain-text or markdown-style extraction. If all mirror services fail or the page requires heavier scraping, fall back to the bundled script and Scrapling.\" \n---\n\n# Markdown Mirror Search\n\nUse this skill for two linked jobs:\n\n1. search the web for candidate pages\n2. turn the chosen page into readable text with a deterministic fallback chain\n\n## Default execution pattern\n\n### A. Search first when the user did not provide a URL\n\n- Use the normal web search tool to find the best candidate URLs.\n- Prefer official sites, documentation pages, primary sources, and stable article links.\n- For multi-source research, collect a short list of URLs, then process them one by one with the readable-content chain below.\n\n### B. Read the page with the fallback chain\n\nUse the bundled script for deterministic behavior:\n\n```bash\npython3 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/skills/markdown-mirror-search/scripts/fetch_readable_url.py '<URL>'\n```\n\nThe script tries, in order:\n\n1. `markdown.new/<original-url>`\n2. `defuddle.md/<original-url>`\n3. `r.jina.ai/...`\n4. `Scrapling`\n\nThe script returns JSON with:\n\n- `ok`\n- `method` (`mirror` or `scrapling`)\n- `source`\n- `requested_url`\n- `resolved_url`\n- `content`\n- mirror attempt diagnostics\n\n## Manual mirror order\n\nIf you are not using the script, follow this order manually:\n\n1. `https://markdown.new/<original-url>`\n2. `https://defuddle.md/<original-url>`\n3. `https://r.jina.ai/http://<original-url-without-scheme>` or `https://r.jina.ai/http://<full-original-url>`\n\nExample:\n\n- Original: `https://example.com/page`\n- Try: `https://markdown.new/https://example.com/page`\n- Then: `https://defuddle.md/https://example.com/page`\n- Then: `https://r.jina.ai/http://https://example.com/page`\n\nTreat a mirror as failed when it returns one of these:\n\n- HTTP error / timeout\n- empty or near-empty body\n- obvious bot-check / challenge page\n- broken formatting that hides the needed facts\n\n## Scrapling fallback\n\nUse Scrapling when the mirror chain does not produce usable content, for example:\n\n- dynamic pages render incomplete content in mirrors\n- article body is missing\n- the site blocks mirror-based extraction\n- the user needs more structured scraping than the mirror output provides\n\nCurrent local integration status:\n\n- Scrapling is expected to be available to `python3`\n- the bundled script already uses it as the final fallback\n\n## Output rules\n\n- Base the answer on the readable content, but cite the original page URL.\n- Mention the mirror URL only for debugging or when the user asks how the content was fetched.\n- Do not invent facts when mirror outputs are partial; explicitly say what is missing.\n- Prefer concise, source-backed summaries.\n- Use the browser only for highly interactive pages, login-gated content, or when search + mirror + Scrapling still fail.\n\n## Trigger examples\n\nThis skill should activate for requests like:\n\n- “搜一下这个网站讲了什么”\n- “帮我查某个网页的内容”\n- “把这个链接转成 markdown 看看”\n- “上网搜一下某个话题，并优先抓可读版本”\n- “这个页面打不开，换个可抓的方式读内容”\n- “先搜索，再把结果网页抓成可读文本”\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773625490711}}
