{"type":"message","id":"f012475a","parentId":"74c30683","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:50:45.074Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the `shouldAutoFallback` method to understand when it falls back to system speech recognition.","thinkingSignature":"985c84c2c4ad97425a02b679b36a1a2668571d41162d5c5385266939f3084be9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dbt4ndpggsgq_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/apps/kids-box-tv-app/app/src/main/java/com/openclaw/kidsboxtv/audio/SpeechPracticeRecognizer.kt","limit":50,"offset":130}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":104395,"output":102,"cacheRead":24336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128833,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773629440628}}
{"type":"message","id":"e889504a","parentId":"f012475a","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:50:45.113Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dbt4ndpggsgq_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"            statusMessage = \"系统里没有可用的语音识别界面（${debugSummary()}）\"\n            null\n        }\n    }\n\n    override fun shouldAutoFallback(error: Int): Boolean {\n        return error == SpeechRecognizer.ERROR_INSUFFICIENT_PERMISSIONS ||\n            error == SpeechRecognizer.ERROR_CLIENT ||\n            error == SpeechRecognizer.ERROR_SERVER\n    }\n\n    override fun reset() {\n        if (isListening) {\n            recognizer?.cancel()\n        }\n        isListening = false\n        lastResult = null\n        lastErrorCode = 0\n        lastErrorAttemptId = 0\n        statusMessage = initialStatus()\n        currentTargetText = \"\"\n        currentTargetLabel = \"\"\n        currentTargetRewardId = \"\"\n        currentAttemptId = 0\n    }\n\n    override fun shutdown() {\n        recognizer?.cancel()\n        recognizer?.destroy()\n        recognizer = null\n    }\n\n    private fun ensureRecognizer() {\n        if (recognizer != null) return\n        recognizer = SpeechRecognizer.createSpeechRecognizer(context).apply {\n            setRecognitionListener(object : RecognitionListener {\n                override fun onReadyForSpeech(params: Bundle?) {\n                    isListening = true\n                    statusMessage = \"开始跟读吧…\"\n                }\n\n                override fun onBeginningOfSpeech() {\n                    isListening = true\n                    statusMessage = \"正在听…\"\n                }\n\n                override fun onRmsChanged(rmsdB: Float) = Unit\n\n                override fun onBufferReceived(buffer: ByteArray?) = Unit\n\n\n[102 more lines in file. Use offset=180 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773629445105}}
{"type":"message","id":"110a2c15","parentId":"e889504a","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:50:57.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the problem better. The issue is:\n\n1. If Sherpa is enabled (SHERPA_ONNX mode), it tries to use Sherpa\n2. If Sherpa fails (e.g., model not ready, audio recording fails), it throws an exception\n3. The exception is caught and sets `statusMessage = \"离线识别暂时不可用：${t.message}\"`\n4. This error message is shown to the user as \"提示：似乎出错了呢\"\n\nThe fallback mechanism in the UI (`shouldAutoFallback`) only works for system SpeechRecognizer errors (ERROR_INSUFFICIENT_PERMISSIONS, ERROR_CLIENT, ERROR_SERVER), NOT for Sherpa exceptions.\n\nSo the problem is that when Sherpa fails, it doesn't automatically fall back to the system recognizer. The user is stuck with the Sherpa error.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to fix this. We need to:\n1. Make Sherpa errors trigger a fallback to system recognizer\n2. Or make Sherpa more resilient\n\nLet me check what the user sees - they said they gave microphone permission, but still got the error. This suggests the Sherpa is failing for some reason (maybe model not ready, or audio recording issue).\n\nActually, looking back at my earlier changes - I added a factory fallback that should switch to system engine if Sherpa model is not ready. But maybe it's not working properly, or there's another issue.\n\nLet me also check if there's an issue with how Sherpa is being initialized - maybe it's crashing before even getting to the recording phase.","thinkingSignature":"eb91b53e427b95de673325e98d108f9fd8b0ecc0280647b80e622c1a99ba31f5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6dyskg2hk5gx_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/apps/kids-box-tv-app/app/src/main/java/com/openclaw/kidsboxtv/audio/SpeechPracticeEngineFactory.kt"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":104844,"output":378,"cacheRead":24336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129558,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773629445117}}
{"type":"message","id":"662bf165","parentId":"110a2c15","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:50:57.794Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6dyskg2hk5gx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"package com.openclaw.englishworkbook.audio\n\nimport android.content.Context\nimport com.openclaw.englishworkbook.data.AppSettingsRepository\nimport com.openclaw.englishworkbook.data.AsrEngineMode\n\nobject SpeechPracticeEngineFactory {\n    fun create(\n        context: Context,\n        settingsRepository: AppSettingsRepository,\n    ): SpeechPracticeEngine {\n        return when (settingsRepository.asrEngineMode()) {\n            AsrEngineMode.SYSTEM -> SpeechPracticeRecognizer(context)\n            AsrEngineMode.SHERPA_ONNX -> {\n                val modelManager = com.openclaw.englishworkbook.data.SherpaOnnxModelManager(context)\n                val sherpaSettings = settingsRepository.sherpaOnnxSettings()\n                val sherpaReady = sherpaSettings.enabled && modelManager.inspect(sherpaSettings.modelId).isReady\n                if (sherpaReady) {\n                    SherpaOnnxSpeechPracticeEngine(context, settingsRepository)\n                } else {\n                    SpeechPracticeRecognizer(context)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773629457788}}
{"type":"message","id":"0a007baf","parentId":"662bf165","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:51:14.959Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the factory is supposed to fall back to system recognizer if Sherpa model is not ready. But the issue is:1. The factory checks if Sherpa is ready using `modelManager.inspect(sherpaSettings.modelId).isReady`\n2. If not ready, it returns `SpeechPracticeRecognizer` (system)\n3. But if the Sherpa *is* marked as enabled but fails at runtime (e.g., audio recording fails), there's no fallback\n\nThe user might have Sherpa enabled but the model is not actually ready (files missing), causing Sherpa to crash.\n\nLet me also check what `initialStatus()` returns for Sherpa when model is not ready - that should tell the user.\n\nActually, the issue is that when Sherpa is selected and the model is NOT ready, the `SherpaOnnxSpeechPracticeEngine` is created but it will fail when trying to record.\n\nWait - the factory DOES check for `sherpaReady` and falls back to system if not ready. So the issue might be:\n\n1. User has Sherpa enabled\n2. Model appears \"ready\" (directory exists) but the actual model files are missing\n3. Sherpa tries to run, fails, shows error\n\nOR\n\n1. There's a bug in how the status is shown\n2. The error message is not being properly handled\n\nLet me add better error handling - make Sherpa failures automatically fall back to system recognizer. Also, let me improve the initial status check.\n\nActually, looking at the code again, I think the issue might be simpler - the Sherpa might be throwing an exception during initialization or startRecording, and that exception is not being caught properly for auto-fallback.\n\nLet me improve the error handling:1. Make Sherpa report errors in a way that triggers auto-fallback\n2. Add better logging\n3. Make sure the UI properly handles Sherpa failures\n\nActually, let me just fix it by making Sherpa failures trigger the fallback. I'll modify the code to catch Sherpa exceptions and treat them as fallback-triggering errors.","thinkingSignature":"bd36edc141a52e01c804b367a0eda09252f5fa1f5ec894a5723d989ab6bb7f48"},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题了。Sherpa 启用但模型未就绪时会崩溃，然后不会自动回退到系统语音。\n\n我来修复这个问题：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xhs77nkfhp6m_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/apps/kids-box-tv-app/app/src/main/java/com/openclaw/kidsboxtv/audio/SherpaOnnxSpeechPracticeEngine.kt","limit":80,"offset":1}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":105450,"output":537,"cacheRead":24336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130323,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773629457796}}
{"type":"message","id":"7a1e85d2","parentId":"0a007baf","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:51:15.000Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xhs77nkfhp6m_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"package com.openclaw.englishworkbook.audio\n\nimport android.content.Context\nimport android.content.Intent\nimport android.os.Handler\nimport android.os.Looper\nimport androidx.compose.runtime.getValue\nimport androidx.compose.runtime.mutableIntStateOf\nimport androidx.compose.runtime.mutableStateOf\nimport androidx.compose.runtime.setValue\nimport com.openclaw.englishworkbook.data.AppSettingsRepository\nimport com.openclaw.englishworkbook.data.SherpaOnnxModelManager\n\nclass SherpaOnnxSpeechPracticeEngine(\n    context: Context,\n    private val settingsRepository: AppSettingsRepository,\n) : SpeechPracticeEngine {\n    private val appContext = context.applicationContext\n    private val modelManager = SherpaOnnxModelManager(appContext)\n    private val mainHandler = Handler(Looper.getMainLooper())\n    private val pcmRecorder = PcmAudioRecorder()\n\n    override var isListening by mutableStateOf(false)\n        private set\n    override var statusMessage by mutableStateOf(initialStatus())\n        private set\n    override var lastResult by mutableStateOf<SpeechPracticeResult?>(null)\n        private set\n    override var lastErrorCode by mutableIntStateOf(0)\n        private set\n    override var lastErrorAttemptId by mutableIntStateOf(0)\n        private set\n\n    private var runtime: SherpaOnnxRuntime? = null\n    private var workerThread: Thread? = null\n    @Volatile\n    private var stopRequested: Boolean = false\n\n    private var currentTargetText: String = \"\"\n    private var currentTargetLabel: String = \"\"\n    private var currentTargetRewardId: String = \"\"\n    private var nextAttemptId: Int = 1\n    private var currentAttemptId: Int = 0\n\n    override fun isAvailable(): Boolean {\n        val settings = settingsRepository.sherpaOnnxSettings()\n        return settings.enabled && modelManager.inspect(settings.modelId).isReady\n    }\n\n    override fun startPractice(targetText: String, targetLabel: String, targetRewardId: String): Boolean {\n        val settings = settingsRepository.sherpaOnnxSettings()\n        val status = modelManager.inspect(settings.modelId)\n        lastResult = null\n        lastErrorCode = 0\n        lastErrorAttemptId = 0\n\n        if (!settings.enabled) {\n            statusMessage = \"sherpa-onnx 尚未启用，请先在设置里打开离线跟读\"\n            return false\n        }\n        if (!status.isReady) {\n            statusMessage = \"sherpa-onnx 模型未就绪：缺少 ${status.missingFiles.joinToString(\", \")}（目录：${status.modelDirPath}）\"\n            return false\n        }\n        if (workerThread?.isAlive == true || isListening) {\n            statusMessage = \"上一轮跟读还没结束，请稍等一下\"\n            return false\n        }\n\n        val normalizedTarget = targetText.trim()\n        if (normalizedTarget.isBlank()) {\n            statusMessage = \"当前题目没有可跟读的英文内容\"\n            return false\n        }\n\n        val currentRuntime = SherpaOnnxRuntime(appContext, status)\n        if (!runCatching { currentRuntime.initialize() }.getOrDefault(false)) {\n            currentRuntime.shutdown()\n            statusMessage = \"离线识别模型初始化失败，请检查模型文件后重试\"\n            return false\n\n[177 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773629474989}}
{"type":"message","id":"4504e925","parentId":"7a1e85d2","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:51:21.466Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the Sherpa engine does check if the model is ready (`status.isReady`) and returns false if not ready. But the error message is not being displayed properly to the user, or there's an issue with how the UI handles this.\n\nActually, looking at the code, when Sherpa fails with `startPractice` returning false, the UI should show the error message. But maybe there's a timing issue or the error is not being properly propagated.\n\nLet me look at the UI code to see how it handles the startPractice result.","thinkingSignature":"48169d8fb7f3913400fccbc0072ef5efb2c8928b988b27799cd6f861e692c4d1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x8fnmq655jir_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"set -e\ncd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\ngrep -n \"startPractice\\|onPracticeClick\" apps/kids-box-tv-app/app/src/main/java/com/openclaw/kidsboxtv/ui/KidsBoxTvApp.kt | head -20","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":106712,"output":230,"cacheRead":24336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131278,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773629475004}}
