{"type":"message","id":"afa8f62d","parentId":"7193575f","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:48:29.153Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Adjusting data class fields**\n\nI need to patch ReadAlongScorer to include both old and new fields along with an enum. I could make the data class fields accommodate both sets and provide default values. Additionally, the WordFeedback should have optional status and score/isCorrect fields. I'll overwrite the file with a merged implementation using the old algorithm, while also considering the totalScore alias. I need to adjust the IFlytek creation to fill in any missing fields or rely on defaults since the score()/Cloud uses different named parameters.**Updating data classes and enums**\n\nI'm looking to rewrite the enum for WordMatchStatus and the data class for WordFeedback, which includes parameters like word, status, score, and isCorrect. The ReadAlongScore class needs several parameters, such as score, totalScore, and various feedback lists. I find that having a default for totalScore referencing prior parameters is possible, and it’s safer to define them explicitly in constructors, although defaults can refer to previous ones. I need to update the IFlytek WordFeedback creation to ensure the status parameter is required and maybe adjust how we define statuses based on totalScore. Additionally, I'll patch the IFlytek mapping to set the status accurately.**Finalizing ReadAlongScorer updates**\n\nI'm considering that recognizedWordFeedback might default to an empty list, which seems practical. I also think that the Cloud engine should compile through the score() method. This means that I’ll need to overwrite the ReadAlongScorer to integrate these changes fully. By making these updates, I’ll ensure that the ReadAlongScorer operates smoothly and includes all necessary adjustments, aligning everything with the new structures and defaults we've set up. Let’s get this finalized!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"我不等别的解释了，直接把 **Trae 改坏的评分数据结构兼容层补回去**，先恢复可编译、可出包。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6uzONOmcI2mJ8H73YSe0z1lb","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/apps/kids-box-tv-app/app/src/main/java/com/openclaw/kidsboxtv/audio/ReadAlongScorer.kt","content":"package com.openclaw.englishworkbook.audio\n\nimport kotlin.math.max\nimport kotlin.math.roundToInt\n\nenum class WordMatchStatus {\n    MATCHED,\n    MISSED,\n    EXTRA,\n}\n\ndata class WordFeedback(\n    val word: String,\n    val status: WordMatchStatus = WordMatchStatus.MATCHED,\n    val score: Int = if (status == WordMatchStatus.MATCHED) 100 else 0,\n    val isCorrect: Boolean = status == WordMatchStatus.MATCHED,\n)\n\ndata class ReadAlongScore(\n    val score: Int,\n    val totalScore: Int = score,\n    val accuracyScore: Int = score,\n    val fluencyScore: Int = 100,\n    val integrityScore: Int = 100,\n    val encouragementTitle: String,\n    val encouragementDetail: String,\n    val targetText: String = \"\",\n    val recognizedText: String = \"\",\n    val matchedWords: Int = 0,\n    val targetWordCount: Int = 0,\n    val recognizedWordCount: Int = 0,\n    val exactMatch: Boolean = false,\n    val targetWordFeedback: List<WordFeedback> = emptyList(),\n    val recognizedWordFeedback: List<WordFeedback> = emptyList(),\n    val rewardStars: Int = 0,\n)\n\nobject ReadAlongScorer {\n    fun score(targetText: String, recognizedText: String): ReadAlongScore {\n        val normalizedTarget = normalize(targetText)\n        val normalizedRecognized = normalize(recognizedText)\n\n        val targetWords = normalizedTarget.split(\" \").filter { it.isNotBlank() }\n        val recognizedWords = normalizedRecognized.split(\" \").filter { it.isNotBlank() }\n        val alignment = alignWords(targetWords, recognizedWords)\n\n        val matchedWords = alignment.matchedPairs.size\n        val recall = if (targetWords.isEmpty()) 0.0 else matchedWords.toDouble() / targetWords.size.toDouble()\n        val precision = if (recognizedWords.isEmpty()) 0.0 else matchedWords.toDouble() / recognizedWords.size.toDouble()\n        val charSimilarity = similarity(normalizedTarget, normalizedRecognized)\n        val exactMatch = normalizedTarget == normalizedRecognized && normalizedTarget.isNotBlank()\n\n        val rawScore = when {\n            exactMatch -> 100.0\n            normalizedRecognized.isBlank() -> 0.0\n            else -> recall * 60.0 + precision * 20.0 + charSimilarity * 20.0\n        }\n        val finalScore = rawScore.roundToInt().coerceIn(0, 100)\n        val rewardStars = when {\n            finalScore >= 95 -> 3\n            finalScore >= 80 -> 2\n            finalScore >= 60 -> 1\n            else -> 0\n        }\n        val encouragementTitle = when {\n            finalScore >= 95 -> \"太棒了\"\n            finalScore >= 80 -> \"很棒\"\n            finalScore >= 60 -> \"接近了\"\n            else -> \"再试一次\"\n        }\n        val encouragementDetail = when {\n            finalScore >= 95 -> \"这次几乎和标准答案一致。\"\n            finalScore >= 80 -> \"大部分都读对了，再稳一点会更好。\"\n            finalScore >= 60 -> \"已经比较接近，重点看看漏掉的词。\"\n            else -> \"先慢一点，把每个词读完整。\"\n        }\n\n        return ReadAlongScore(\n            score = finalScore,\n            totalScore = finalScore,\n            accuracyScore = finalScore,\n            fluencyScore = 100,\n            integrityScore = 100,\n            encouragementTitle = encouragementTitle,\n            encouragementDetail = encouragementDetail,\n            targetText = targetText,\n            recognizedText = recognizedText,\n            matchedWords = matchedWords,\n            targetWordCount = targetWords.size,\n            recognizedWordCount = recognizedWords.size,\n            exactMatch = exactMatch,\n            targetWordFeedback = targetWords.mapIndexed { index, word ->\n                WordFeedback(\n                    word = word,\n                    status = if (index in alignment.matchedTargetIndexes) WordMatchStatus.MATCHED else WordMatchStatus.MISSED,\n                    score = if (index in alignment.matchedTargetIndexes) 100 else 0,\n                    isCorrect = index in alignment.matchedTargetIndexes,\n                )\n            },\n            recognizedWordFeedback = recognizedWords.mapIndexed { index, word ->\n                WordFeedback(\n                    word = word,\n                    status = if (index in alignment.matchedRecognizedIndexes) WordMatchStatus.MATCHED else WordMatchStatus.EXTRA,\n                    score = if (index in alignment.matchedRecognizedIndexes) 100 else 0,\n                    isCorrect = index in alignment.matchedRecognizedIndexes,\n                )\n            },\n            rewardStars = rewardStars,\n        )\n    }\n\n    private fun normalize(text: String): String {\n        return text\n            .lowercase()\n            .replace(\"'\", \"\")\n            .replace(Regex(\"[^a-z0-9 ]\"), \" \")\n            .replace(Regex(\"\\\\s+\"), \" \")\n            .trim()\n    }\n\n    private data class AlignmentResult(\n        val matchedPairs: List<Pair<Int, Int>>,\n        val matchedTargetIndexes: Set<Int>,\n        val matchedRecognizedIndexes: Set<Int>,\n    )\n\n    private fun alignWords(targetWords: List<String>, recognizedWords: List<String>): AlignmentResult {\n        if (targetWords.isEmpty() || recognizedWords.isEmpty()) {\n            return AlignmentResult(emptyList(), emptySet(), emptySet())\n        }\n\n        val dp = Array(targetWords.size + 1) { IntArray(recognizedWords.size + 1) }\n        for (i in targetWords.indices.reversed()) {\n            for (j in recognizedWords.indices.reversed()) {\n                dp[i][j] = if (targetWords[i] == recognizedWords[j]) {\n                    dp[i + 1][j + 1] + 1\n                } else {\n                    max(dp[i + 1][j], dp[i][j + 1])\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        var i = 0\n        var j = 0\n        val pairs = mutableListOf<Pair<Int, Int>>()\n        while (i < targetWords.size && j < recognizedWords.size) {\n            when {\n                targetWords[i] == recognizedWords[j] -> {\n                    pairs += i to j\n                    i += 1\n                    j += 1\n                }\n                dp[i + 1][j] >= dp[i][j + 1] -> i += 1\n                else -> j += 1\n            }\n        }\n\n        return AlignmentResult(\n            matchedPairs = pairs,\n            matchedTargetIndexes = pairs.map { it.first }.toSet(),\n            matchedRecognizedIndexes = pairs.map { it.second }.toSet(),\n        )\n    }\n\n    private fun similarity(a: String, b: String): Double {\n        if (a.isBlank() && b.isBlank()) return 1.0\n        val distance = levenshtein(a, b)\n        val base = max(a.length, b.length).coerceAtLeast(1)\n        return (1.0 - distance.toDouble() / base.toDouble()).coerceIn(0.0, 1.0)\n    }\n\n    private fun levenshtein(a: String, b: String): Int {\n        if (a == b) return 0\n        if (a.isEmpty()) return b.length\n        if (b.isEmpty()) return a.length\n\n        val previous = IntArray(b.length + 1) { it }\n        val current = IntArray(b.length + 1)\n\n        for (i in a.indices) {\n            current[0] = i + 1\n            for (j in b.indices) {\n                val cost = if (a[i] == b[j]) 0 else 1\n                current[j + 1] = minOf(\n                    current[j] + 1,\n                    previous[j + 1] + 1,\n                    previous[j] + cost,\n                )\n            }\n            for (k in previous.indices) {\n                previous[k] = current[k]\n            }\n        }\n\n        return previous[b.length]\n    }\n}\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773650853083}}
