{"type":"message","id":"b38f47be","parentId":"2ee3c394","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:20:38.461Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring recovery options**\n\nI need a quick recovery plan. Using Python's requests library with an unverified SSL context could simplify things. But, hmm, maybe it’s even easier to use curl with a manually encoded query. I’m weighing these options—Python might give me more flexibility, but curl could be quicker for this specific task. Let’s try using Python with an unverified SSL context for accessing grep.app and see how that turns out!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"我继续查正确握手格式，换成忽略证书校验的搜索方式，不停在 404 这个点上。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_qTpx9dXXUqJA0XVBGsLL954G","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.parse, urllib.request, json, ssl\nctx=ssl._create_unverified_context()\nqueries=[\n  'spark-openapi.cn-huabei-1.xf-yun.com api/v1/voice-insight',\n  'voice-insight xfyun websocket api/v1',\n  'spark-openapi voice-insight websocket',\n]\nfor q in queries:\n    url='https://grep.app/api/search?q='+urllib.parse.quote(q)\n    print('\\n===',q,'===')\n    try:\n        data=json.load(urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=20, context=ctx))\n        hits=data.get('hits',{}).get('hits',[])\n        print('total_hits', len(hits))\n        for h in hits[:5]:\n            print(h.get('repo',{}).get('raw','?'), h.get('path','?'))\n            sn=h.get('content',{}).get('snippet','')\n            print(sn[:300])\n            print()\n    except Exception as e:\n        print('ERR',e)\nPY","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":1000,"timeout":120}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773652823332}}
